CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 26, 1952, pg. 3 reads: "Children Start Plant-Up Drive - Herron Hill students are shown as they began planting a plot near the Herron Hill Reservoir this week in initial phases of the annual citywide spring "Clean-up, Paint-up, Plant-up" campaign. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women and children, including two girls on left holding poster that reads "Plant a Garden", planting in a plot near Herron Hill Reservoir, for annual citywide campaign; "Clean-up, Paint-up, Plant-up," another version
